{"parentUuid":"8f595cf6-f2e1-43e7-88e1-bd107c1edd01","isSidechain":false,"message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01A1DkW7RcBhmqa79SbJrRHb","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"That's great! The Claude Code JetBrains plugin works with PyCharm (and other JetBrains IDEs). Here's what you can do with it:\n\n**Key features:**\n- Run Claude Code directly from within PyCharm without switching to a terminal\n- The Claude Code panel appears as a tool window in your IDE\n- Full access to all Claude Code capabilities (file editing, code explanation, debugging, etc.)\n\n**Getting started:**\n1. Open the Claude Code tool window (usually via **View > Tool Windows > Claude Code** or the sidebar icon)\n2. Authenticate if prompted\n3. Start chatting or giving it tasks — it has context of your open project\n\n**Tips:**\n- You can highlight code in the editor and ask Claude Code to explain or refactor it\n- Use `@filename` to reference specific files in your prompts\n- The plugin syncs with the same session as the CLI, so your settings carry over\n\nIs there something specific you're trying to do with the plugin, or are you running into any issues setting it up?"}],"stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":3,"cache_creation_input_tokens":5463,"cache_read_input_tokens":13923,"output_tokens":291,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":5463,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[{"input_tokens":3,"output_tokens":291,"cache_read_input_tokens":13923,"cache_creation_input_tokens":5463,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":5463},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"}},"requestId":"req_011CaGQiBBKzfPjZ8sjw46bj","type":"assistant","uuid":"c6163093-48c9-47b7-8506-7d7ad0504fb6","timestamp":"2026-04-21T06:03:03.541Z","userType":"external","entrypoin