{"parentUuid":"734f5ab6-abf5-4097-be58-8a138bc1cfa5","isSidechain":false,"message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01Hhad8RM3opCFVy6hMvnsi4","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Try these steps to get it showing:\n\n**1. Restart PyCharm fully**\nClose and reopen PyCharm completely after installing the plugin.\n\n**2. Check the plugin is actually enabled**\n- Go to **File > Settings > Plugins**\n- Click the **Installed** tab\n- Search for **Claude Code** and make sure the checkbox is **enabled**\n\n**3. Look for it in other places**\n- Check the right/left/bottom sidebars for a small tab labeled \"Claude Code\"\n- Try **View > Tool Windows** and scroll through the full list\n\n**4. Make sure Claude Code CLI is installed**\nThe JetBrains plugin requires the Claude Code CLI to be installed first. Open a terminal and run:\n```\nclaude --version\n```\nIf it says \"command not found\", you need to install the CLI first from [claude.ai/code](https://claude.ai/code) before the plugin will work.\n\nWhich of these did you find? Especially let me know if the CLI is installed or not — that's the most common reason the tool window doesn't appear."}],"stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":3,"cache_creation_input_tokens":93,"cache_read_input_tokens":20035,"output_tokens":289,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":93,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[{"input_tokens":3,"output_tokens":289,"cache_read_input_tokens":20035,"cache_creation_input_tokens":93,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":93},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"}},"requestId":"req_011CaGR1p3b1GLdVQh1L16mp","type":"assistant","uuid":"ce947a2b-9687-4ab2-b25f-d318181a7de1","timestamp":"2026-04-21T06:07:02.193Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"C:\\